  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Community Development Project for Morang, Sunsari, and Rautahat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will assist a total of 1,100 families in the Morang, Sunsari and Rautahat Districts of Nepal, which are characterized by widespread poverty, caste discrimination and illiteracy, among other problems. The 400 original project families will receive 300 meat goats, 200 pigs, 100 water buffaloes, fodder seed/saplings, funds for crop seeds and to lease 5 hectares of land. The respective local groups will receive funding to purchase fruit and vegetable seed/saplings. An additional 700 families will benefit though &#x201C;passing on the gift.&#x201D;  All project participants will receive trainings on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, self-help group management, improved animal management, gender justice,  kitchen gardening and organic farming, forage feed production, reproductive health and HIV/AIDS awareness. Heifer will also train village animal health workers (VAHW) and provide basic veterinary equipment and vet supplies. Exchange visits will be organized for project participants to learn from other Heifer project sites.</narrative>
  </description>
